        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/lee-zeldin-epa-biden-green-new-scam-claim.jpg" alt="Joe Biden imposed these restrictions to advance the climate change cult and the green new scam, according to Lee Zeldin, the EPA administrator" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF"> 
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>
             Joe Biden imposed these restrictions to advance the climate change cult and the green new scam, according to Lee Zeldin, the EPA administrator. Credits: REUTERS/Jim Urquhart</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
       
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px " font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          The Trump administration's Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) plans to repeal <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-14-jun-25-sotw-h1-1-power-plant-pollution-standards?source=website" target="_blank">power plant pollution standards</a>. These standards originally required plants to reduce harmful emissions, such as carbon dioxide and mercury. The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-14-jun-25-sotw-h1-2-epa?source=website" target="_blank">EPA</a> asserts that rolling back the standards will cut back operators $1.2B annually, lower consumer expenses, promote energy independence, and support AI-driven manufacturing.</p>
        
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          Critics say this is misleading. Independent analysis shows the rules would have delivered $370B in climate and health benefits by the 2040s, cutting over 1B tons of CO₂. A University of Maryland study warns the rollback could cause 22,800 additional deaths and $1.1T in GDP losses by 2035 due to increased pollution.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
          Experts say the reversal benefits a “tiny group” of wealthy plant operators and fossil fuel donors. At the same time, Americans will face dirtier air, more asthma attacks, and greater climate risks. Despite the EPA’s assertions of economic benefit, it provides little proof that deregulation will meaningfully reduce consumer expenses. </p>
        </mj-text> 
